#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:44
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "In the upper part of this control module you can see several tabs: "
#| "<guilabel>Focus</guilabel>, <guilabel>Titlebar Actions</guilabel>, "
#| "<guilabel>Window Actions</guilabel>, <guilabel>Moving</guilabel> and "
#| "<guilabel>Advanced</guilabel>. In the <guilabel>Focus</guilabel> panel "
#| "you can configure how windows gain or lose focus, &ie; become active or "
#| "inactive. Using <guilabel>Titlebar Actions</guilabel> and "
#| "<guilabel>Window Actions</guilabel> you can configure how titlebars and "
#| "windows react to mouse clicks. <guilabel>Moving</guilabel> allows you to "
#| "configure how windows move and place themselves when started. The "
#| "<guilabel>Advanced</guilabel> options cover some specialized options like "
#| "<quote>window shading</quote>."
msgid ""
"In the upper part of this control module you can see several tabs: "
"<guilabel>Focus</guilabel>, <guilabel>Titlebar Actions</guilabel>, "
"<guilabel>Window Actions</guilabel>, <guilabel>Movement</guilabel> and "
"<guilabel>Advanced</guilabel>. In the <guilabel>Focus</guilabel> panel you "
"can configure how windows gain or lose focus, &ie; become active or "
"inactive. Using <guilabel>Titlebar Actions</guilabel> and <guilabel>Window "
"Actions</guilabel> you can configure how titlebars and windows react to "
"mouse clicks. <guilabel>Movement</guilabel> allows you to configure how "
"windows move and place themselves when started. The <guilabel>Advanced</"
"guilabel> options cover some specialized options like <quote>window shading</"
"quote>."
msgstr ""
"Sur la partie supérieure du module de configuration, vous pouvez voir "
"plusieurs onglets : <guilabel>Focus</guilabel>, <guilabel>Actions de la "
"barre de titre</guilabel>, <guilabel>Actions de la fenêtre</guilabel>, "
"<guilabel>Déplacement</guilabel> et <guilabel>Avancé</guilabel>. Dans le "
"panneau <guilabel>Focus</guilabel>, vous pouvez configurer de quelle manière "
"les fenêtres prennent ou perdent le focus, &cad; deviennent actives ou "
"inactives. Les onglets <guilabel>Actions de la barre de titre</guilabel> et "
"des <guilabel>Actions de la fenêtre</guilabel> vous permettent de configurer "
"de quelle manière la barre des titres et les fenêtres réagissent aux clics "
"de souris. L'onglet <guilabel>Déplacement</guilabel> vous permet de "
"configurer de quelle manière la fenêtre se déplace et se place elle même au "
"démarrage. L'onglet <guilabel>Avancé</guilabel> couvre certaines options "
"spécialisées comme les ombres de fenêtres</quote>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:59
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Please note that the configuration in this module will not take effect if "
#| "you do not use &kde;'s native window manager, &kwin;. If you do use a "
#| "different window manager, please refer to its documentation for how to "
#| "customize window behavior."
msgid ""
"Please note that the configuration in this module will not take effect if "
"you do not use &plasma;'s native window manager, &kwin;. If you do use a "
"different window manager, please refer to its documentation for how to "
"customize window behavior."
msgstr ""
"Veuillez remarquer que la configuration de ce module ne prendra pas effet si "
"vous n'utilisez pas le gestionnaire de fenêtre natif de &kde;, &kwin;. Si "
"vous utilisez un autre gestionnaire de fenêtre, référez vous à sa "
"documentation pour personnaliser le comportement des fenêtres."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:68
#, no-c-format
msgid "Focus"
msgstr "Focus"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:70
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "The <quote>focus</quote> of the desktop refers to the window which the "
#| "user is currently working on. The window with focus is often referred to "
#| "as the <quote>active window</quote>."
msgid ""
"The <quote>focus</quote> of the workspace refers to the window which the "
"user is currently working on. The window with focus is often referred to as "
"the <quote>active window</quote>."
msgstr ""
"Le <quote>focus</quote> du bureau concerne la fenêtre sur laquelle "
"l'utilisateur travaille. La fenêtre avec le focus est souvent indiquée comme "
"la <quote>fenêtre active</quote>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:76
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Focus does not necessarily mean the window is the one at the front &mdash; "
"this is referred to as <quote>raised</quote>, and although this is "
"configured here as well, focus and raising of windows are configured "
"independently."
msgstr ""
"Le focus ne veut pas nécessairement dire que la fenêtre est celle en avant "
"plan. Elle est indiquée comme <quote>Placée dessus</quote>, bien qu'elle est "
"configurée ici correctement, le focus et le placement au dessus de la "
"fenêtre est configuré indépendamment."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:84
#, no-c-format
msgid "Windows activation policy"
msgstr "Stratégie d'activation des fenêtres"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:86
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "There are six methods &kde; can use to determine the current focus:"
msgid "There are six methods &kwin; can use to determine the current focus:"
msgstr ""
"Il y a six méthodes que &kde; peut utiliser pour déterminer le focus "
"courant : "

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:93
#, no-c-format
msgid "Click to focus"
msgstr "Cliquer pour donner le focus"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:95
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A window becomes active when you click into it. This behaviour is common on "
"other operating systems and likely what you want."
msgstr ""
"Une fenêtre devient active lorsque vous cliquez dessus. Ce comportement est "
"classique avec d'autres systèmes d'exploitation et correspond probablement à "
"ce que vous voulez."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:102
#, no-c-format
msgid "Click to focus (mouse precedence)"
msgstr "Cliquer pour obtenir le focus (Précédence de la souris)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:104
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "This is mostly the same as <guilabel>Click To Focus</guilabel>. If an "
#| "active window has to be chosen by the system (&eg; because the currently "
#| "active one was closed) the window under the mouse is the preferred "
#| "candidate. Unusual, but possible variant of <guilabel>Click To Focus</"
#| "guilabel>."
msgid ""
"This is mostly the same as <guilabel>Click to focus</guilabel>. If an active "
"window has to be chosen by the system (&eg; because the currently active one "
"was closed) the window under the mouse is the preferred candidate. Unusual, "
"but possible variant of <guilabel>Click to focus</guilabel>."
msgstr ""
"C'est très similaire à <guilabel>Cliquer pour avoir le focus</guilabel>. Si "
"une fenêtre active doit être choisie par le système (&pex; lorsque la "
"fenêtre active a été fermée), la fenêtre sous la souris est la candidate "
"toute désignée. C'est un cas assez inhabituel, mais une variante possible de "
"<guilabel>Cliquer pour avoir le focus</guilabel>."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:115
#, no-c-format
msgid "Focus follows mouse"
msgstr "Le focus suit la souris"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:117
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Moving the mouse pointer actively over a normal window activates it. New "
#| "windows such as the mini command line invoked with <keycombo action="
#| "\"simul\">&Alt;<keycap>F2</keycap></keycombo> will receive the focus, "
#| "without you having to point the mouse at them explicitly. &eg; windows "
#| "randomly appearing under the mouse will not gain the focus. Focus "
#| "stealing prevention takes place as usual. Think as <guilabel>Click To "
#| "Focus</guilabel> just without having to actually click."
msgid ""
"Moving the mouse pointer actively over a normal window activates it. New "
"windows such as the mini command line invoked with <keycombo action=\"simul"
"\">&Alt;<keycap>F2</keycap></keycombo> will receive the focus, without you "
"having to point the mouse at them explicitly. &eg; windows randomly "
"appearing under the mouse will not gain the focus. Focus stealing prevention "
"takes place as usual. Think as <guilabel>Click to focus</guilabel> just "
"without having to actually click."
msgstr ""
"Déplacer activement le pointeur de souris sur une fenêtre normale l'active. "
"Les nouvelles fenêtres tel que la ligne de commande appelée avec <keycombo "
"action=\"simul\">&Alt;<keycap>F2</keycap></keycombo> va recevoir le focus, "
"sans avoir à placer explicitement le pointeur de souris sur celle-ci. Par "
"exemple, les fenêtres apparaissant de façon aléatoire sous la souris ne "
"recevront pas le focus. La prévention de vol de focus est appliquée de façon "
"classique. Pensez comme <guilabel>cliquer pour avoir le focus</guilabel> "
"juste sans avoir à cliquer vraiment."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:126
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In other window managers, this is sometimes known as <quote>Sloppy focus "
"follows mouse</quote>."
msgstr ""
"Dans d'autres gestionnaires de fenêtres, la fonctionnalité est parfois connu "
"sous <quote>La souris suit le focus mollement</quote>."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:134
#, no-c-format
msgid "Focus follows mouse (mouse precedence)"
msgstr "Le focus suit la souris (Précédence de la souris)plus"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:136
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "This is mostly the same as <guilabel>Focus Follows Mouse</guilabel>. If "
#| "an active window has to be chosen by the system (&eg; because the "
#| "currently active one was closed) the window under the mouse is the "
#| "preferred candidate. Choose this, if you want a hover controlled focus."
msgid ""
"This is mostly the same as <guilabel>Focus follows mouse</guilabel>. If an "
"active window has to be chosen by the system (&eg; because the currently "
"active one was closed) the window under the mouse is the preferred "
"candidate. Choose this, if you want a hover controlled focus."
msgstr ""
"Ceci est globalement identique à <guilabel>Le focus suit la souris</"
"guilabel>. Si une fenêtre active doit être sélectionnée par le système (par "
"exemple lorsque la fenêtre active a été fermée), la fenêtre sous la souris "
"est la candidate toute désignée. Choisissez ceci, si vous voulez un focus "
"piloté par le survol."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:147
#, no-c-format
msgid "Focus under mouse"
msgstr "Focus sous la souris"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:149
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "The window that happens to be under the mouse pointer becomes active. If "
#| "the mouse is not over a window (for instance, it's on the desktop) the "
#| "last window that was under the mouse has focus. New windows such as the "
#| "mini command line invoked with <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Alt;"
#| "<keycap>F2</keycap></keycombo> will not receive the focus, you must move "
#| "the mouse over them to type."
msgid ""
"The window that happens to be under the mouse pointer becomes active. If the "
"mouse is not over a window (for instance, it's over the desktop wallpaper) "
"the last window that was under the mouse has focus. New windows such as the "
"mini command line invoked with <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Alt;<keycap>F2</"
"keycap></keycombo> will not receive the focus, you must move the mouse over "
"them to type."
msgstr ""
"La fenêtre qui se trouve sous le pointeur de souris devient active. Si la "
"souris ne se trouve pas sur une fenêtre (par exemple se trouve sur le "
"bureau), la dernière fenêtre qui était sous la souris a le focus. Les "
"nouvelles fenêtres tel que la ligne de commande appelée avec <keycombo "
"action=\"simul\">&Alt;<keycap>F2</keycap></keycombo> ne reçoivent pas le "
"focus. Vous devez déplacer votre souris dessus pour saisir du texte."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:160
#, no-c-format
msgid "Focus strictly under mouse"
msgstr "Le focus est strictement sous la souris"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:162
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Similar to <guilabel>Focus Under Mouse</guilabel>, but even more strict "
#| "with its interpretation. Only the window under the mouse pointer is "
#| "active. If the mouse pointer is not over a window, no window has focus. "
#| "New windows such as the mini command line invoked with <keycombo action="
#| "\"simul\">&Alt;<keycap>F2</keycap></keycombo> will not receive the focus, "
#| "you must move the mouse over them to type."
msgid ""
"Similar to <guilabel>Focus under mouse</guilabel>, but even more strict with "
"its interpretation. Only the window under the mouse pointer is active. If "
"the mouse pointer is not over a window, no window has focus. New windows "
"such as the mini command line invoked with <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Alt;"
"<keycap>F2</keycap></keycombo> will not receive the focus, you must move the "
"mouse over them to type."
msgstr ""
"Identique à <guilabel>Le focus est sous la souris</guilabel> mais plus "
"strict dans son interprétation. Seul la fenêtre sous le pointeur de souris "
"est active. Si le pointeur de souris n'est pas sur une fenêtre, aucune "
"fenêtre n'a le focus. Les nouvelles fenêtres tel que la ligne de commande "
"appelée avec <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Alt;<keycap>F2</keycap></keycombo> "
"ne reçoivent pas le focus. Vous devez déplacer votre souris dessus pour "
"saisir du texte."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:176
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Note that <guilabel>Focus Under Mouse</guilabel> and <guilabel>Focus "
#| "Strictly Under Mouse</guilabel> prevent certain features, such as "
#| "<guilabel>Focus stealing prevention</guilabel> and the <keycombo action="
#| "\"simul\">&Alt;&Tab;</keycombo> walk-through-windows dialog, from working "
#| "properly."
msgid ""
"Note that <guilabel>Focus under mouse</guilabel> and <guilabel>Focus "
"strictly under mouse</guilabel> prevent certain features, such as "
"<guilabel>Focus stealing prevention</guilabel> and the <keycombo action="
"\"simul\">&Alt;&Tab;</keycombo> walk-through-windows dialog, from working "
"properly."
msgstr ""
"Remarquez que <guilabel>Le focus est sous la souris</guilabel> et "
"<guilabel>Le focus est strictement sous la souris</guilabel> empêche "
"certaines fonctionnalités comme <guilabel>la prévention de vol de focus</"
"guilabel> et la boîte de dialogue pour naviguer entre les fenêtres par "
"<keycombo action=\"simul\">&Alt;&Tab;</keycombo> de fonctionner correctement."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:188
#, no-c-format
msgid "Delay focus by"
msgstr "Temporiser le focus de"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:190
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is the delay after which the window the mouse pointer is over will "
"automatically receive focus."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:197
#, no-c-format
msgid "Focus stealing prevention"
msgstr "Prévention du vol de focus"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:199
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This option specifies how much KWin will try to prevent unwanted focus "
"stealing caused by unexpected activation of new windows."
msgstr ""
"Cette option spécifie jusqu'à quel point KWin tentera d'empêcher un vol de "
"focus non souhaité, causé par une activation inattendue de nouvelles "
"fenêtres."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:207
#, no-c-format
msgid "None"
msgstr "Aucun"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:208
#, no-c-format
msgid "Prevention is turned off and new windows always become activated."
msgstr ""
"La prévention est désactivée et les nouvelles fenêtres sont toujours "
"activées."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:212
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guilabel>Low</guilabel>"
msgstr "<guilabel>Bas</guilabel>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:213
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Prevention is enabled; when some window does not have support for the "
"underlying mechanism and KWin cannot reliably decide whether to activate the "
"window or not, it will be activated. This setting may have both worse and "
"better results than the medium level, depending on the applications."
msgstr ""
"La prévention est activée ; lorsqu'une fenêtre ne gère pas le mécanisme sous-"
"jacent et que KWin ne peut pas décider de manière fiable s'il doit activer "
"la fenêtre ou non, celle -ci sera activée. Ce réglages peut avoir des "
"résultats meilleurs ou pires que le niveau moyen, en fonction des "
"applications."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:220
#, no-c-format
msgid "Medium"
msgstr "Moyen"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:221
#, no-c-format
msgid "Prevention is enabled."
msgstr "La prévention est activée."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:225
#, no-c-format
msgid "High"
msgstr "Haut"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:226
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"New windows get activated only if no window is currently active or if they "
"belong to the currently active application. This setting is probably not "
"really usable when not using mouse focus policy."
msgstr ""
"Les nouvelles fenêtres ne sont activées que si aucune fenêtre n'est "
"actuellement active ou si elles appartiennent à l'application actuellement "
"active. Ce réglage n'est probablement pas vraiment utilisable lorsque la "
"règle de focus de la souris n'est pas utilisée."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:233
#, no-c-format
msgid "Extreme"
msgstr "Extrême"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:234
#, no-c-format
msgid "All windows must be explicitly activated by the user."
msgstr ""
"Toutes les fenêtres doivent être explicitement activées par l'utilisateur."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:239
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Windows that are prevented from stealing focus are marked as demanding "
"attention, which by default means their taskbar entry will be highlighted. "
"This can be changed in the Notifications control module."
msgstr ""
"Les fenêtres empêchées de voler le focus sont marquées comme demandant "
"l'attention, ce qui par défaut signifie que leur entrée dans la barre des "
"tâches sera mise en surbrillance. Ceci peut être modifié dans le module de "
"configuration des notifications."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:248
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "Raising window"
msgid "Raising windows"
msgstr "Mise sur le dessus des fenêtres"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:250
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Besides receiving focus, you can also control under which conditions windows "
"get raised, &ie; brought to the front."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:254
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You should make sure that at least one of the raising options is enabled, "
"otherwise windows will not be raised at all."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:258
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guilabel>Click raises active window</guilabel> will bring a window to the "
"front when it is clicked on. This is enabled by default with a click to "
"focus policy."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:262
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "With a hover to focus policy you can alternatively use auto raise. By "
#| "placing a mark in front of <guilabel>Raise on hover, delayed by</"
#| "guilabel>, &kde; can bring a window to the front if the mouse is over "
#| "that window for a specified period of time. You can determine the delay "
#| "for this option by using the spin box control."
msgid ""
"By activating <guilabel>Raise on hover, delayed by</guilabel> you can "
"alternatively bring a window to the front if the mouse pointer is over that "
"window for a specified period of time. You can determine the delay for this "
"option by using the spin box control. This auto-raising option is only "
"available with a hover to focus policy."
msgstr ""
"Avec la stratégie de fournir le focus par un survol, vous pouvez utiliser "
"alternativement la mise en avant automatique. En cochant la case "
"<guilabel>Mettre en avant lors d'un survol, temporisé de</guilabel>, &kde; "
"peut placer la fenêtre au dessus des autres si celle-ci est survolée par le "
"pointeur de la souris pendant une période de temps déterminée. Vous pouvez "
"déterminer le délai pour cette option en utilisant la boîte de dialogue."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:267
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Setting the delay too short will cause a rapid fire changing of windows, "
"which can be quite distracting. Most people will like a delay of 100-300 ms. "
"This is responsive, but it will let you slide over the corners of a window "
"on your way to your destination without bringing that window to the front."
msgstr ""
"Configurer le délai trop court provoquera un changement trop rapide de "
"fenêtre. qui peut être assez gênant. La plupart des personnes aime un délai "
"compris entre 100 et 300ms. L'action répond correctement, mais cela vous "
"laisse le temps d'aller vers les coins d'une fenêtre de votre choix sans "
"amener cette fenêtre en premier plan."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:279
#, no-c-format
msgid "Multiscreen behavior"
msgstr "Comportement multi-écran"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:281
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This controls the behavior of window focus with multiple screens. Note that "
"these options appear only when more than one screen is currently connected."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:288
#, no-c-format
msgid "Separate screen focus"
msgstr "Séparer le focus des écrans"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:290
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When this option is enabled, focus operations are limited only to the active "
"screen. For instance, when you close a window, then the next window to "
"receive focus will be a window on the active screen, even if there is a more "
"recently used window on a different screen."
msgstr ""

